text.tspan: Number of suicides per 100,000 people in a given population and year. Suicide deaths are underreported in many countries due to social
stigma and cultural or legal concerns. This data is adjusted for this underreporting to estimate the actual rate of suicides.
Data source: WHO, Global Health Observatory (2022)
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is age-standardized.
